radiographic_examinations.findings: 13 mm appendix demonstrates a hyperemic wall surrounded by inflammatory changes/fat stranding; no evidence of free air, abscess, or appendiceal rupture. Right adnexal slightly complex cyst consistent with a hemorrhagic follicle. Left ovary contains follicular activity. Lung bases and cardiac apex are unremarkable aside from minimal dependent atelectasis. Liver, spleen, gallbladder, portal vein, pancreas, abdominal aorta, and kidneys are unremarkable. Small bowel normal in course and caliber. Stomach contains food contents and contrast. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic lesions in bones.
